Sentencas: The physicochemical properties for layered perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+delta (PBSCF) oxide are systematically investigated to gain insight into the correlation between structure, surface state and oxygen reduction reaction properties.
Titulo: Characterization and functional application of PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ cathode material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The PBSCF sample possesses orthorhombic structure and keeps better structural stability under operating conditions.
Titulo: Characterization and functional application of PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ cathode material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: X-ray photoelectron spectra analysis indicates that the mixed oxidation state of (Co, Fe) and Pr promotes the oxygen reduction reaction kinetics by creating oxygen vacancies at the surface.
Titulo: Characterization and functional application of PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ cathode material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Mossbauer Spectroscopy affirms that the proportion of Fe3+ and Fe4+ in iron species is 79.1 % and 20.9 %, respectively.
Titulo: Characterization and functional application of PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ cathode material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The electrode polarization resistance is 0.067 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Characterization and functional application of PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ cathode material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The oxygen-ion bulk diffusion plays the rate-limiting step during the electrode process.
Titulo: Characterization and functional application of PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ cathode material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The cell with PBSCF cathode delivers the power density of 590 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Characterization and functional application of PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ cathode material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: These results show the PBSCF exhibits a promising application prospect in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Characterization and functional application of PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ cathode material for IT-SOFC
